  "text": "The case of a ¼ 1 is equivalent to the case of the classic M-vector where the distance between the maturity of each cash flow and the planning horizon is raised to integer powers (e.g., ðt À H Þ 1 ; ðt À H Þ 2 ; ðt À H Þ 3 ; . . .). [CITATION_1] provide empirical evidence supporting this model using a planning horizon of four years. Our empirical tests not only confirm their findings, but also extend their model by considering other values of a equivalent to cases where the distance between some polynomial function of the maturity of each cash flow and that of the planning horizon, is raised to integer powers (e.g., a ¼ 0:5 produces ðt 0:",
